Four persons died in an auto crash on the Lagos â€“ Epe expressway on Sunday. The accident involved a Toyota Camry and a stationary tricycle. The speeding car, with registration number LSR 724 FW, lost a tyre and rammed into a man washing his tricycle. The vehicle then somersaulted into a ditch. Director General, Lagos State Emergency Management Agency (LASEMA), Olufemi Oke-Osanyintolu, told NAN that the accident occurred at 5 p.m. He confirmed that all the three adult male occupants in the car and the tricycle rider lost their lives. Emergency responders and police officers from Odo-Noforija Divisional Headquarters evacuated the corpses to Epe General Hospital.